  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3507d679efa283143b52308c9a6a3292, type: 3}
  m_Name: Module_3_Set_Q2
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::QuestionData
  question: Fill in the blank. Data that is not completely raw and contains elements
    such as tags and organizational metadata is known as _____.
  answers:
  - semi-structured data
  - true data
  - unstructured data
  - structured data
  maxSelections: 1
  correctAnswerIndices: 00000000
  correctMessage: "Semi-structured data is the \u201Cbridge\u201D between structured
    and unstructured data. It does not have a predefined data model and is more complex
    than structured data, yet easier to store than unstructured data. Semi-structured
    data uses metadata to identify specific data characteristics and scale data into
    records and preset fields."
  incorrectMessage: "Semi-structured data is the \u201Cbridge\u201D between structured
    and unstructured data. It does not have a predefined data model and is more complex
    than structured data, yet easier to store than unstructured data. Semi-structured
    data uses metadata to identify specific data characteristics and scale data into
    records and preset fields."
